### 🔷 3. The OODA Loop — How General Agents Reason

OODA comes from military strategy (John Boyd). General agents operate in a continuous OODA loop — this is what separates them from simple chatbots:

| Step | What It Means in Agent Context |
|---|---|
| **O — Observe** | Agent reads your problem, scans the repo/files, gathers context |
| **O — Orient** | Agent frames the problem within constraints (your tech stack, requirements, limits) |
| **D — Decide** | Agent chooses an approach — what to build, what tools to use |
| **A — Act** | Agent writes code, runs commands, calls tools, produces output |
| ↩️ **Loop** | Agent reviews its own output, detects errors, and repeats until solved |

> "General Agents observe your problem, orient around constraints, decide on an approach, act by writing code or running commands, and correct their mistakes — repeating until the problem is solved."

**Claude Code vs. a Coding Agent — Key Distinction:**

| | Coding Agent (e.g., Cursor) | General Agent (Claude Code) |
|---|---|---|
| Scope | Software development only | ANY business domain |
| Identity | Developer's pair programmer | Digital employee |
| Built For | Developers | Anyone solving problems |
| Example | "Implement this feature" | "Why did sales drop in Q3?" |

> "Calling Claude Code a 'Coding Agent' is like calling a CEO an 'Email Writer' just because they use email."

