### 🔷 4. The Five Powers of Autonomous Agents

These five capabilities are what transform an LLM (a passive predictor) into an autonomous agent (an active actor). **Know these by name — exam favourite!**

| Power | What It Means | Example |
|---|---|---|
| **1. See** | Perceive inputs — text, images, documents, data | Reading an invoice PDF, scanning a codebase |
| **2. Hear** | Process audio/voice inputs | Voice commands, speech-to-text transcription |
| **3. Reason** | Think through multi-step problems, plan, decide | Decomposing "reduce churn by 15%" into sub-tasks |
| **4. Act** | Execute actions — call APIs, write files, run code, send emails | Creating a Jira ticket, querying a database |
| **5. Remember** | Persist information across sessions via memory systems | Recalling previous client preferences, past interactions |

> Without all Five Powers, an AI is just a chatbot. With all five, it becomes a Digital FTE.

