### 🔷 6. The AIFF Standards Ecosystem

AIFF = **AI Factory Foundation Standards** — the three protocols that make Digital FTEs interoperable and scalable:

| Standard | Full Name | What It Does |
|---|---|---|
| **MCP** | Model Context Protocol | Universal connector — links agents to live data (CRM, SQL, Slack, APIs). The "With-What." |
| **AGENTS.md** | Agent Specification File | Markdown file defining what an agent can do, its constraints, tools & behavior |
| **Agent Skills** | SKILL.md files | Modular folders teaching an agent a specific repeatable workflow. The "How-To." |

**How MCP + Skills work together:**
- **Skills** = the expertise (domain knowledge encoded in SKILL.md)
- **MCP** = the connectivity (live data access)
- Together: plug in a Finance MCP + Finance Skill → Finance Agent. Plug in Sales MCP + Sales Skill → Sales Agent

> "Skills provide the expertise. MCP provides the connectivity. Together, they turn a General Agent into a specialized Digital FTE."

